caption: So we went for Restaurant Week The young lady that answered the phone didn't know where you could park and the food was just ok. We passed so many places to get here for the food to be just ok. The wings were good but everything else was not. It was our first time trying it and it was not crowded and service was still slow. The mac and cheese needs a reboot and they did not have the banana pudding why advertise it and not have the items listed on the menu I could see if it was the end of restaurant week not a good experience.
Wonderful people and service, great atmosphere, and view of stadium. Food was delicious. Need to expand beer options.

This place was nice. I came here for restaurant week. My waitress was so nice and helpful. The food  Presentation was nice. The only thing I really had a problem with was the food was not seasoned so the food was bland but the cornbread,fries and banana pudding were delicious.
Food & service were excellent.

I think I was here at the wrong time! The inside was really cold in the first place. In terms of food, I ordered baby back ribs per my waitress suggestion. But it was too dry! The staff and customer care was great and the prices are reasonable. I’ll try again next time to see if I was wrong about the food.
huge portions and loved the live music! great place for a quick bite when you’re in wrigleyville

I give it two stars only because it didn’t produce a gag reflex. We ordered the taste of the daddy. The ribs tasted and textured like beef jerky on a bone and the smokey flavor was so overbearing. If you like to chew gum I suggest the ribs.  The macaroni and cheese tasted like melted play-do. I’m pondering what cheese is it’s actually made with?  “It’s a waste of space in my stomach”, my shared dinner partner said. I will never be ordering it again.

Being harassed  for what?? over a sandwich? Act like a man and grow some testicles please

The food and the owner Doug are outstanding. My cousin ordered for her son's graduation party,a we highly recommend it. He even has his own special drinks to go along with it. Thanks Doug your the best!!  10 🌟 🌟

I ordered the pulled pork sandwich and it was very tasty and melted in my mouth. I definitely recommend this establishment. I didn't give 5 stars because i haven't tried the full menu yet.

Great BBQ in Wrigley. Bar is really nice, staff is super friendly. Pulled pork is good, definitely recommend upgraded to Carolina style.... Slaw is some of the best I've had. Go for the oit beans as well. Will not be disappointed.
Fantastic burnt ends. Creamy, delicious mac. The beans are great as well, especially if you like chili.

Good bbq.  Had a freak...smoked corn beef on rye.  Added some of their bbq mustard.  Also a burnt end sandwich.  Great sandwiches and the fries were excellent.  Their mac n cheese left a little to be desired.

We came here for father's day, and the hostess were a bit rude, we didn't get a friendly greeting and having been a hostess for years I know that the first impression sets the mood for the rest of the visit and we'll it wasn't a great one. But other than that our waitress was awesome, very helpful, the food was pretty great and loved the outdoor upstairs patio. We had the nachos which were alright, and then we shared a plate with ribs, pulled pork and brisket. It came with two sides so we got fries && Mac n cheese. The Mac n cheese lacked a little bit of flavor. I got a Moscow mule and honestly I don't drink often but Moscow mules are my go to and I couldn't even taste the alcohol but alright fine it was okay. Overall a decent expirience if we didn't have such a rude welcoming at the begining it would have been great.

I have never threw a whole meal away. I bought the smoke wings and Mac and Cheese to go. There was no cutlery or napkins in my bag but I let it slide. The wings were nasty!! There was no flavor and the skin was slimy and not in the normal smoked wings way. The Mac and cheese tasted like it came out a box with some extra seasoning that was not suppose to be added. I was so disappointed that I threw my money away. Lesson learned I should have listen to the stranger I asked when they said the food was not good.
Good food, staff are very accommodating, even to families. Directly across from the field too.

Overpriced.  .  Undercooked chicken.  Chicken was on a 55 dollar platter.  They replaced the chicken but also took our entire tray of food and didnt replace it.  I had a rack of ribs, burnt tips and brisket still on the tray that I didnt get to finish and still paid 55 dollars for it.

Great tasting barbeque. The tips and brisket were a bit fattier than I prefer but the meat was super tender and delicious. The beans were amazing and the corn bread was the best I've ever had.
Our waiter Brian was amazing ! Great service and the drinks he made us were the BOMB ! Very friendly & knowledgeable when it came down to food allergies.  -Bubbles Window Washing Staff Thank you ! (:

Visited last night, so not busy, due to the off season. Drinks: My Southern Sweet tea cocktail was mainly water. The regular tea was basically brown water. Music: The music was entertaining but VERY loud for the space. Had to yell my order to the waiter. Food: Two people in my party ordered the Burnt Ends. The meat was not cut properly and undercooked. Flavor was bland and VERY tough. The mac n cheese tasted like a #2 pencil. The Beer cheese and pretzel appetizer was really tasty. Service: The greeters were very nice. Our waiter, Kevin, was more interested in watching the basketball game than waiting on any of his tables. Never saw him accomplish a 2 step process thru the whole night. Very distracted and inattentive. When my husband was ordering his meal, he told Kevin that he only wanted one of the 2 sides. Kevin said, "it comes with 2 so you have to pick 2". Seems kinda odd. For my daughter, who is a HUGE Cub's fan, we wanted to give her an amazing 16th birthday experience in Chicago, and dinner left much to be desired. For a $70+ meal for 3 people, we expected more.
Great place. Friendly attentive staff. That cornbread is a MUST. I promise you will have more than one maybe two additional peices of cornbread. Its that good. You've been warned =P
You gotta put all sauces on at the same time.

on the pricey side for barbeque but hits the spot

I love me some bbq and smoke daddy has some seriously good bbq.  I ordered the 2 smoked meats (brisket and chicken) with a side of Mac and cheese and cornbread.  The highlight of the night was the brisket and cornbread. Man that stuff just melts in your mouth.  I wasn't the biggest fan of the chicken so if I had to do it again would have ordered a different meat.  We came on a Friday night and there was live blues music which was absolutely great.  That being said, it was a bit loud and I would recommend getting a seat on the top floor if there's a band playing.  Still loud enough to hear but also have a conversation.

I look at the register and there are 4 staff members watching the game on TV. The service was horrible. I and my party left without ordering because the staff failed to greet the customer.

The staff is friendly and attentive. The original BBQ sauce is cumin-heavy - the sweet & smoky is recommended. The rib tips wew fat-heavy but very tender. The cornbread has caramel flavors and nice crumble. Highly recommended after a day at Wrigley Field.

i just love this space!! the atmosphere, energy and the food kicks butt! service is attentive from entry throughout service!  i was here when they opened, and have enjoyed them several times since.  have yet to enjoy the other location/s.  i enjoy the live music when they have it - the bottomless bloody Marys (served with a rib, no joke) & the mimosas are a great deal!  and the fact that you can switch for your bottomless beverage is quite FAB!  i do prefer the glass carafes that were used early on for the O.J. and the bubbly, tho i can see how those would end up broken or lost - the plastic cups were a tad tacky, tho it does not stop me from enjoying the place... the brisket, burnt ends, ribs, the sides, & the brunch bottomless platter of food - OH MY!!! offered on Saturdays and Sundays!  enjoy!

This 2 story bbq joint is amazing!  Very well constructed, with planar TV setups for large screen viewing of sports and news. Menus were easy to choose from (not an overload of options like cheesecake factory), and everything on their menu was delicious. They offer indoor and outdoor seating.  The 2nd floor opens up completely to bring in outdoor air, and it is 70% covered but also has a pergola stretched over a portion for more sun and closer views of the Wrigley Stadium. Waitress and hostess were nice, quick, and courteous.  We didnt come on a game day, so it wasn't busy.  Service might be strained during game days - but that's understandable. Their cocktails were great.  I had a bourbon shot with a pickle juice chaser (they named it something clever and I just had to try it ^.^) which I highly recommend. Bbq sauce is left at the table for everyone to help themselves, and every single sauce is unique and delicious.  My favorite is probably their original.
Great food, nice place to watch a game and friendly service!

The space is beautiful and spacious. The food and service were great...we did go on a rainy slow night, but I can imagine how crowded this may get during the cubs season. We were happy to get a chance to enjoy the space and the food! We had both types of ribs, pulled pork sandwiches,  corn bread which was awesome and their sweet potato fries. Let's not forget the different beers on tap and local brews! Everything was great! Parking is a bit challenging but that's why you take an uber, Lyft or taxi! Spothero saved our day!  Enjoy!

Great place to go after the game. Might be a wait but the food is good and the views are great. Your sitting right across the street from beautiful Wrigley Field and it's a great place to people watch and relax after the game. The one item I was very impressed with was the macaroni and cheese. Our server recommend it and she was spot on. I know they're know for the BBQ but definitely get the mac and cheese. Our server couldn't tell us what made it special so you know it's gotta be good. The one negative thing was the BBQ nachos appetizer. It looks so good but it was a disappointment to me. Not enough meat. I got the brisket sandwich for my meal and it was great so I recommend it too. Overall a great place.
Meat cold and so so. Not horrible at all, just not great. Cornbread top notch.
Great beer menu good food and great service the only downside to this place is you need to get there super early on game day to get a seat but that's everywhere on Clark.

I had the BBQ pulled chicken it was good just a little dry. The coleslaw was not the best tasted better on my sandwich. Staff was friendly and food was ready fast.
Don't eat meat, but love the veggie burger

Took my 2 year old son for (both of our) first game at Wrigley, and one of the ushers recommended Smoke Daddy. Initially, I only ordered a sandwich and a side to split with my son.  Then my server (Jeff, who was great) advised me that kids eat free before (I think) 6:30. Sweet! Ordered my son his own meal, and fed both of us for a bill of under $15, with leftovers.  They even included a scoop of ice cream for dessert with my son's free meal! I expected to drop $30-40 to feed both of us anything other than fast food in downtown Chicago.  Food was great, and our meal was served no longer than 5 minutes after ordering (not just a perk, but a huge convenience when out to eat with a 2 year old). As much as I like trying new places I've never been before, I was so impressed that I will be back next time I'm at a game.  Go Cubs!
Went back the next day....!!!
Love the sidewalk seats looking out at Wrigley, the nachos were tremendous
First time in. Fast food out. !
Delicious!
Food was good. Excellent service. Only downside was the long walk to the bathroom.

The good: + The burnt ends were fatty and moist. I'd get this on a return visit. + The sauces are tasty. Four different types cover mustard, Kansas City style, hot Texas, and Texas. + The cornbread was interesting. It was pretty creamy and it was a generous portion.  The fine: The beans were good but unremarkable. The fries were a little too salty but hot and crispy. The mac and cheese was inoffensive. Not a particularly deep flavor nor did it have any bite (it was a bit mushy).  The not as good: - This was the thinnest sliced brisket I've ever seen, and it was dried out. I'm really curious as to the reasoning behind this. I was actually really surprised they served such dried out product. I would hope that in most places, if it's that dried out, it wouldn't be served. - There was a bit of plastic in my burnt ends. The manager came to see us and apologize, and they gave us a few bucks off of our order. I'm okay with how they dealt with it; I was hoping there'd be a bigger comp for chewing on plastic but I'm glad they didn't argue with us. - Slow service. The waiter was great; really friendly and he gave great suggestions. But there were two servers for the entire second floor. It took longer than I would have liked to get his attention for the plastic and check. (I went on a Monday afternoon).  Summary: I'd go back because at the end of the day I was satisfied with my meal. The value is decent and hey it's tasty barbecue. There were missteps in service but they cared enough to correct them.

A pleaseant surprise for sure. The food was great. We had a cheeseburger and a salad and they were both really good. They had live music and accommodated a large party right away. Service was standard. Would go back.

The volume level of the TVs was unbearable. Do not go on a Friday night. Food was great. Service was great. Go on a week night.

This place has pretty good bbq. We came here while visiting family and was a little hesitant as we’re from KC, home of the best bbq. I was pleasantly surprised with the taste of their meats, especially their burnt ends. The atmosphere was also really cool. We’ll definitely be back the next time we’re in town!
Smoke Daddy does meat fantastically! I would highly suggest trying their food.
Tough, dry brisket

Ordered takeout here. Ribs had a wierd smell and the BBQ baked beans were loaded with this skin-like substance. Will never eat here again. It was so bad i'm even considering not chancing it at the Wicker Park location as well (which I used to love). Note to owner: this was delivery ordered the evening of 12/16 around 7:55PM via Caviar App
Great BBQ, great views, good beer
Really good beef biscuit
Hell yes.

Love the atmosphere.  Great location across from Wrigley Field.   Love the spacious two level setup with the outside patio.  Mac and cheese is amazing! Love the soft pretzels and chips with jalapeno beer cheese dip.  Restaurant was a bit chilly for early December but that was our only complaint.  We would definitely return.

Good service and good (not great) food. The nachos with burnt ends were particularly good. Would get 4 stars but the restaurant was very cold (was there in mid Nov.) and it doesn't make for pleasant dining when you can't take your coat off...
Would be a five star rating but exterior door were propped open so every time someone came in, so did a big woosh of COLD air. Bad policy of propping them open management needs to change that.
Amazing space, great food, great prices and Awesome Service!
Great food and service.  A fun place to catch up with friends.
Service was good and the ribs were good but I've had better ribs.
Food and service was great.  My first visit and the waiter gave great recommendations.

Great restaurant, amazing BBQ entrees, appetizers that could be entrees and drinks that are enough to write home about. The bloody, old fashioned and definitely the Dickle Pickle are great if you want to have a good time.
I really enjoyed the Daddy o sandwich, definitely grab the cornbread it's all of the Yaassss!
Nice place, good food, good beer, good service, good live music.
Ribs had less flavour than what we make at home
Great place for a bite after a Cubs game. Smoked chicken wings were excellent.

1 star for the restaurant but we would give Sara the bartender 5 stars. We had a terrible experience with no one waiting on us for an hour. Despite telling 2 other people on the staff this information, we continued to have no one wait on us. But when Sara came over and we told her what happened, she immediately apologized and went to get a piece of paper to take our orders, despite the fact that she was running the bar. Without her, it would've been a zero star experience. We hope Sara is recognized for this! She is management material!
Nice place good service. Super clean bathroom!!
BBQ and blues are a great combination.
Was here for a Cubs game, had my 10yr old with us. They text you when the table was ready; which gave us time to shop. food was "okay" staff was friendly. i'd go back
Great food, service and atmosphere!
Good BBQ, but had to sit next to Lauren Schaller.   Wouldn't recommend.
Great brunch option before the Cubs game! Kid friendly. We sat outside and enjoyed bottomless mimosas and an enormous amount of food. Service was awesome too. We will be back!
Great place to meet friends. Great BBQ everything. The cornbread is to die for....
Really good bbq! The place is huge and service is on point! It can get a bit loud with the band playing if you’re sitting downstairs. The mules (cocktails) are all great!
Food is great. Just dont expect waitstaff that cares. Subpar service that was borderline rude.

Very rude waitress, she came over and Instead of being polite, she barked at me, that I was at a reserved table.... I hadn't been approached previously so I thought she would take my drink order but instead spit fire at me and walked …
Some of the best BBQ I’ve had.  Ribs were outstanding.

St. Louis Style Ribs were made to perfection. I usually make my own St. Louis ribs with my own sauce, however after a friend shared his experience here before a Chicago Cubs baseball game I tried them over the All Star break and they were better than my own. The chicken and vegetable soup was so well prepared and healthy I ordered some to take home. This in my opinion is their best product that is correct even better than the ribs in my experience.  The place is very clean and sanitary with well attended to restrooms with plenty of hot water. The entire staff and management team coordinate well and provide an exceptional dining experience. The cookies are amazing. Attend!!!!!!
I really love this place

4.8/5 stars for this new Wrigleyville location of Smoke Daddy. Service, food, and the live blues were all excellent. Don’t miss the chicken wings, baby back ribs, or the mac n cheese. Brisket was good but maybe just a little too fatty. Beer list is short but is quality. The live blues was excellent and the floor to ceiling windows give you an almost surreal view of iconic Wrigley Field. Lots of competition out there but their combination of superior quality barbecue, energetic blues, views of THE ballpark, and great service are a recipe for success.
I went after the Cubs game and ordered take out. The meal was delicious and the staff was professional and nice. I felt at home. I will go here again.
Great place
We went on a non cubs weekend day. Had a great view of the park across the street. The adult cherry coke was delicious. Food was typical bbq, didn’t blow my mind.

Really good food for great prices! I came here with my dad before a cubs game and we were shocked by the prices and food quality. We had three appetizers and a couple drinks for under $30. Total steal! Better than the places next door.
We had a brisket sandwich which was loaded with fat. We also had ribs which were so so. The sauces were nothing special.

I went here for the VIP private Crown Royal Texas Mesquite launch party.  Barbeque, blues, drinks and more!  This location is right across the street from Wrigley Field.  No, you will not be able to watch a Cubs game from here, but they have a lot of big screen TV's where you can watch a variety of sports.  I'm sure they feature the Cubs games while they are playing.  We were here on a Wednesday night and the first floor was half full!  Not bad for a week night.  They are really crowded on weekends and during Cub home  games.  Our event was on the second floor, with a full bar, lots of tables, and a great rooftop/balcony space that overlooks Clark street.  Two levels of great barbecue, music and drinks!  We had a wonderful buffet of salad, cornbread, rolls, smoked meats: chicken, brisket, and pork, macaroni and cheese, barbecue beans and smores for dessert.  Everything was delicious with a great smoky flavor.  All of the meats were tender and moist.  They have 3 choices of hot sauce on the tables, but, I felt that the meat was so good, that they didn't need any sauce at all.  I definitely will return here for the food, music and drinks!

Been here a few times since they opened.  Had a group of 30 before a game.  Katie - who handles the events - was spot on with planning & overseeing the event.  Her staff was personable,  attentive & expedient with service.  Food was great.  I've been a season ticket holder for years & this place offers value in a great casual venue as convenient as it gets to Wrigley.  Will be a regular stop with or without a group before & after games.
Not my favorite bbq.  Very fast service!!!

Favorite band was playing there Monday night and so decided to try it out for dinner too. Very nicely done, from cornbread to burnt ends to brisket all well prepared and flavorful. Service was great, there were four of us chatting and in no rush, very accomodating. Prices were great, oh that band was the Cash Box Kings.

I was in Wrigleyville around 1PM Saturday and there were three hosts/hostesses gathered around the hostess stand chatting with one another.  This is always a terrible sign, as restaurants that require three people to seat a guest - or where the staff prefers chatting with each other to serving - are usually in serious disrepair.  I wanted to grab a quick bite before my 2:30 PM tour of Wrigley Field so I asked for a table for one.  Ignoring my request, the hostess gave me her best stewardess "over there somewhere" point and told me to go figure it out myself in the bar.  Okay, but why are three people standing there to tell me to seat myself?  I didn't want to sit on a barstool to eat my BBQ but the place wasn’t that busy so I sat at a table that seemed a little out of the way.  I read the menu and made my selection which was easy because it was a very limited selection:  5 sandwiches, 3 types of ribs, 3 types of salads, and some appetizers.  I was actually hoping for BBQ chicken, which would seem like something you might be able to get at a BBQ place, but other than a pulled chicken sandwich I didn’t see any chicken.  I waited.  I waited.  I waited some more.  I was thinking I might have to ditch this place because no one was coming.  Fortunately they solved the problem as a hostess came up to bounce me off my table because it was “reserved”.   Okay, but:  1) There was no reserved sign on it. 2) I had ASKED FOR A TABLE and had not been told to go find one myself, and then reprimanded for my selection. 3) I wasted 10 minute waiting for you not to come help me, but to tell me to go find somewhere else to sit.  Seriously?  Memo to Smoke Daddy’s:  As near I could tell your entire second floor wasn't open (or at least, not open to me, when I specifically ASKED FOR A TABLE!!).  Don’t close half the place then mark off a huge chunk of your remaining seats as RESERVED with an invisible rope line only you can see and then tell people to go seat themselves, because guess what’s going to happen?  Realizing at this point I was doomed I said, “No worries” and left.  I didn’t feel like I should have to argue to get a table or plead to get someone to wait on me and I certainly didn’t want to interrupt their fascinating conversations with each other.   If that's how they handle seating thank goodness I didn't eat any of the food, but fortunately getting seated was so dreadful I never got past the hostess stand.  I sincerely hope they close soon and are replaced with a restaurant with a functional staff.

Food was cold and it wasn't even busy. Very disappointed, good thing the division location has never let me down. I forgot my rule of not visiting a place that has recently opened. Server was very nice.

Tender BBQ, live music, and drinks on multiple levels just across the street from Gallagher Way (formerly The Park at Wrigley) and Wrigley Field. It's a nice place to stop in before or after a game for decently priced BBQ. The bartenders and servers are quick!

Great place to stop before or after the game. Try the Freak Sandwich! Terrific corned beef brisket, a favorite from the Wicker Park location. Quick, with good price point and right across from Wrigley. Live entertainment was a pleasant surprise on a Thursday. Lani was our server, Quick and friendly - I Will Be Back.

Food was outstanding!! Service (Jodie) was outstanding!! Price (value) for the amount of food was outstanding!! Cocktails were outstanding!! The only complaint was that I was visiting from Las Vegas and there isn't one here!!

Overpriced drinks - the Old Fashioned was lackluster. They ran out of burnt ends (no surprise) and ribs (huge surprise). It took us over an hour to get our food. They’re clearly having some issues with operations, which is a shame since they have an incredible location. I won’t be returning.

We came here for dinner on Sunday and it exceeded expectations. They have a live band (everyday apparently) which made it a cool atmosphere and when they are on break, they play classic rock, which is a nice change of pace from other restaurants that only play top 40 music.  The drinks are top notch. The old-fashion is very good along with the seasonal slushee mint julep. They are a bit expensive but it’s worth it for a casual drink. The food is also very good (also a bit on the pricier side but you are paying for great quality of food).  I recommend coming here to grab a bite to eat or to have some beer and listen to good music and watch sports.
After being frozen out of Wrigley Field, Smoke Daddy’s was REALLY warm!  The pulled pork and pulled chicken rocked!  The band was great.  Tons of TV screens to watch the Cubs!
Great BBQ and I'm enjoying this new row of great restaurants!  They have a 2nd level open balcony with seating facing the stadium. I can't wait until it warms up!
